ZH: 1. 他常常用咒骂的词语来伤害别人。
EN: 1. He often uses curse words to hurt others.
ZH: 2. 她竟然对我咒骂了一番。
EN: 2. She actually cursed at me.
ZH: 3. 请不要对长辈使用咒骂的话语。
EN: 3. Please refrain from using curse words towards elders.
ZH: 4. 我无法容忍你对我咒骂。
EN: 4. I cannot tolerate you cursing at me.
ZH: 5. 她受到他咒骂的时候，眼中闪烁着忍耐的火焰。
EN: 5. When she was being cursed at by him, a flame of patience flickered in her eyes.
ZH: 6. 当他生气时，他会不经意地咒骂。
EN: 6. When he gets angry, he unintentionally curses.
ZH: 7. 别人的无礼行为导致了她的咒骂。
EN: 7. The impolite behavior of others led to her cursing.
ZH: 8. 对于那些经常咒骂的人，我们应该保持距离。
EN: 8. We should keep our distance from people who frequently curse.
ZH: 9. 在生气的时候，我们容易失去理智而开始咒骂。
EN: 9. When angry, we are prone to losing our rationality and start cursing.
ZH: 10. 他克制住了自己的咒骂冲动。
EN: 10. He restrained his urge to curse.
ZH: 11. 他以咒骂批评我，使我感到很受伤。
EN: 11. He criticized me with curses, which hurt me deeply.
ZH: 12. 他咒骂着离开了房间，生气地砸上门。
EN: 12. He cursed as he stormed out of the room, slamming the door angrily.
ZH: 13. 我很后悔自己那一番咒骂的话语。
EN: 13. I regret the curse words I uttered.
ZH: 14. 咒骂只会助长仇恨，没有任何好处。
EN: 14. Cursing only fuels hatred, with no benefits whatsoever.
ZH: 15. 她用咒骂的方式来发泄自己的情绪。
EN: 15. She vents her emotions by cursing.
ZH: 16. 她对着镜子里的自己咒骂，发泄内心的不满。
EN: 16. She curses at herself in the mirror, expressing her inner dissatisfaction.
ZH: 17. 我不喜欢被任何人咒骂，无论是谁。
EN: 17. I dislike being cursed at by anyone, no matter who they are.
ZH: 18. 咒骂并不能解决问题，只会激起更多的争端。
EN: 18. Cursing doesn't solve problems; it only sparks more disputes.
ZH: 19. 这个小孩通常用咒骂的话语对待其他同学。
EN: 19. This child usually treats other classmates with curse words.
ZH: 20. 我在他的咒骂下默默地走开，没有回应他的指责。
EN: 20. I silently walked away from his curses, without responding to his accusations.
